---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Power Grab TX — Who's Really Paying for the AI Boom in Texas?">
  <section class="hero">
    <h2>
      Texas Is Paying the Price for the AI Boom
    </h2>
    <p>
      Tech giants are racing to plant massive data centers across Texas — draining the power grid, 
      straining water supplies, and reshaping communities. PowerGrab TX follows the money, the 
      megawatts, and the impact on the people living next door.
    </p>
    <a href="/stay-informed" class="btn">
      Stay informed about AI's impact in Texas
    </a>
  </section>

  <div class="intro">
    <p>
      PowerGrab TX tracks the real cost of AI data centers in Texas — on the grid, 
      the water table, and the communities in their shadow.
    </p>
  </div>

<section class="home-cards-section">
  <h2>Key Issues at a Glance</h2>
  <div class="home-cards">

    <div class="home-card">
      <h3>What's Driving the Power Surge</h3>
      <hr />
      <ul>
        <li>Tech companies buying Texas land at unprecedented speed</li>
        <li>Massive campuses straining water systems and local infrastructure</li>
        <li>Development moving faster than public oversight</li>
        <li>Rapid expansion of AI and cloud data center campuses</li>
        <li>Rising demand for water, cooling, and transmission capacity</li>
        <li>Construction outpacing regional planning</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/right-now#power-surge" class="home-card-link">Dig into the power surge →</a>
    </div>

    <div class="home-card">
      <h3>AI Data Centers Across Texas</h3>
      <hr />
      <ul>
        <li>Data centers rising with little public visibility into their impact</li>
        <li>From hyperscale campuses to high-density compute sites</li>
        <li>Where major data center campuses are being built</li>
        <li>The companies driving Texas' data center boom</li>
        <li>Water use, land impact, and environmental considerations</li>
        <li>Why Texas has become a national hub for AI infrastructure</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/right-now#data-centers" class="home-card-link">See what's being built →</a>
    </div>

    <div class="home-card">
      <h3>Infrastructure Under Pressure</h3>
      <hr />
      <ul>
        <li>Water systems, roads, and transmission corridors being stretched</li>
        <li>Projects bypassing traditional planning timelines</li>
        <li>Cities scrambling to support growth they didn't initiate</li>
        <li>Local permitting challenges and fast-tracked approvals</li>
        <li>Transmission lines, substations, and land-use conflicts</li>
        <li>Rising costs for cities supporting large industrial sites</li>
      </ul>
     <a href="/right-now#infrastructure" class="home-card-link">Follow the infrastructure strain →</a>
    </div>

    <div class="home-card">
      <h3>Impact on Texas Communities</h3>
      <hr />
      <ul>
        <li>Noise, traffic, and vanishing open land affecting residents</li>
        <li>Consequences communities never voted for</li>
        <li>Tax incentives flowing to companies, not locals</li>
        <li>Water usage concerns and environmental trade-offs</li>
        <li>Loss of rural character and open land</li>
        <li>Growing public pushback and local political battles</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/right-now#communities" class="home-card-link">Hear from affected communities →</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

  <section class="posts-section">
    <h2>Latest Posts From Power Grab TX</h2>
    <div class="posts-list">
      <div class="post">
        <h3>
          <a href="/posts/transforming-texas"
            >How AI Data Centers Are Transforming Texas</a>
        </h3>
        <p class="date">May 25, 2026</p>
        <p>
          How AI Data Centers are transforming Texas communities across the
          state, reshaping local economies, environmental policy, and the
          reliability of the Texas power grid...
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="post">
        <h3>
          <a href="/posts/billion-dollar-boom"
            >Billion-Dollar Boom: Texas AI Data Centers in 2026</a>
        </h3>
        <p class="date">May 23, 2026</p>
        <p>
          Texas is rapidly becoming one of the most important locations in the
          United States for AI-focused data centers. With abundant land,
          competitive power markets, and a business-friendly environment...
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="post">
        <h3>
          <a href="/posts/exploding-in-texas"
            >Why AI Data Centers Are Exploding in Texas — And What It Means for
            the Grid</a>
        </h3>
        <p class="date">May 17, 2026</p>
        <p>
          Texas AI data centers are expanding at a historic pace in 2026, making
          the state the epicenter of America's AI infrastructure boom. Over the
          past three years...
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Texas AI Data Centers</h2>
    <details open>
      <summary>What are Texas AI Data Centers?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Texas AI data centers are large facilities that house powerful computers
        used to train and run artificial intelligence systems. They process
        massive amounts of data for cloud services, automation, and machine
        learning applications.
      </div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Why are so many AI data centers being built in Texas?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Texas offers abundant land, relatively low electricity costs, a
        business-friendly regulatory environment, and existing power
        infrastructure — making it an attractive location for large-scale AI
        infrastructure investment.
      </div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do AI data centers affect the Texas power grid?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Yes. AI data centers consume enormous amounts of electricity, and their
        rapid expansion is placing significant strain on the ERCOT grid, raising
        concerns about reliability and costs for all Texas residents.
      </div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do AI data centers use a lot of water?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Many data centers use water-based cooling systems that can consume
        millions of gallons per day. In water-stressed regions of Texas, this
        raises serious concerns about long-term water availability for residents
        and agriculture.
      </div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How do AI data centers impact local communities?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Communities near data centers often experience increased truck traffic,
        24/7 construction noise, changes to rural land character, and rising
        infrastructure costs — while the promised economic benefits don't always
        materialise locally.
      </div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Where can I stay updated on new developments?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Sign up on our <a href="/stay-informed">Stay Informed</a> page to receive
        updates on new data center projects, policy changes, and community impacts
        across Texas.
      </div>
    </details>
  </section>

  <div class="closing">
    <p>
      Texas residents need to understand how this explosive growth in AI
      infrastructure will affect energy costs, the power grid, and local
      communities. Stay informed — the changes coming in the next few years will
      impact everyone.
    </p>
  </div>
  <script>
    const details = document.querySelectorAll("details");
    details.forEach((detail) => {
      detail.addEventListener("toggle", () => {
        if (detail.open) {
          details.forEach((other) => {
            if (other !== detail) other.open = false;
          });
        }
      });
    });
  </script>
</Layout>
<style>
  /* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         MOVE TO → src/pages/index.astro
         Homepage hero, intro, cards, closing CTA.
         ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */

      .hero {
        background: #1a3a6a;
        padding: 3rem 2rem;
        margin: 0.5rem;
        border-radius: 15px;
        color: #fff;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .hero h2 {
        font-size: 2.2rem;
        font-weight: 800;
        max-width: 700px;
        margin: 0 auto 1rem;
        line-height: 1.25;
      }
      .hero p {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        max-width: 680px;
        margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }
      .intro {
        padding: 2rem 2rem 0;
        margin: 0 auto;
        max-width: 700px;
      }
      .intro p {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: 1.6;
        max-width: 680px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .cards {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
        gap: 0.5rem;
      }
      @media (max-width: 900px) {
        .cards {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        }
      }
      @media (max-width: 600px) {
        .cards {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
      }

      .home-cards-section {
        padding: 2rem 2rem 3rem;
        max-width: 1400px;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }

      .home-cards-section > h2 {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        padding-top: 1rem;
        border-top: 2px solid #e05c2a;
        color: #b03a1a;
      }

      .home-cards {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
      }

      .home-card {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        border: 1px solid #e8c9b0;
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 1rem;
        box-sizing: border-box;
        background-color: #fff8f4;
      }

      .home-card h3 {
        font-size: 1rem;
        min-height: 3.5rem;
        margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
        color: #b03a1a;
      }

      .home-card hr {
        border: none;
        border-top: 1px solid #e8c9b0;
        margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
      }

      .home-card ul {
        flex: 1;
        padding-left: 1.2rem;
        margin: 0;
      }

      .home-card ul li {
        margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: #3a2010;
      }

      .home-card-link {
        display: block;
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: #e05c2a;
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      .home-card-link:hover {
        color: #b03a1a;
      }

      @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .home-cards {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
      }

      @media (min-width: 769px) and (max-width: 1024px) {
        .home-cards {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
        }
      }

      .closing {
        background: #1a1a2e;
        color: #fff;
        padding: 3rem 2rem;
        margin: 2rem;
        border-radius: 12px;
      }
      .closing p {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: 1.5;
        max-width: 100%;
      }
       /* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         MOVE TO → wherever your FAQ section lives
         (e.g. src/pages/index.astro if FAQ is on homepage, or its own page —
         check which page actually renders <details>/.faq-section first)
         ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */

      .faq-section {
        padding: 2rem;
        max-width: 820px;
      }
      .faq-section h2 {
        font-size: 1.6rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        text-align: center;
      }
      details {
        border: 1px solid #ddd;
        border-radius: 6px;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        overflow: hidden;
      }
      details[open] {
        border-left: 4px solid #1a4a8a;
      }
      summary {
        padding: 1rem 1.2rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 1rem;
        cursor: pointer;
        list-style: none;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
      }
      summary::after {
        content: "⌄";
        font-size: 1rem;
        color: #666;
      }
      details[open] summary::after {
        content: "⌃";
      }
      .faq-answer {
        padding: 0 1.2rem 1rem;
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: #333;
      }
</style>
